The python-deltasigma project aims to provide a python package fully
compatible with Richard Schreier's MATLAB Delta Sigma Toolbox
(aka delsigma), a specialized Matlab(R) toolkit.

All original MATLAB code is Copyright (c) 2009, Richard Schreier.

The Python code here provided is a derivative work from the above toolkit
and subject to the same license terms.

This package contains some source code from pydsm, also based on the
same MATLAB toolbox. The pydsm package is copyright (c) 2012, Sergio Callegari.

When not otherwise specified, the source code is Copyright 2013,
Giuseppe Venturini and the python-deltasigma contributors.

The Python code here distribued is a derivative work from the MATLAB Delta
Sigma Toolbox and it is distributed under the same license terms.

MATLAB is a registered trademark of The MathWorks, Inc.

Original license follows.

